Rice A’ghetti
Makes 6 to 8 servings

¼ cup butter or margarine
1 cup uncooked rice
½ cup spaghetti, broken into very small pieces
½ small onion, chopped
3 cups water 
1 tablespoon instant chicken bouillon crystals or 1 cube

1.  In a large saucepan, melt butter.
2. Add rice, spaghetti, and onion; cook and stir mixture on medium heat until spaghetti is golden brown.
3. Add water and bouillon.
4. Cover; simmer over low heat for 25 – 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and spaghetti and rice are tender.
5. Serve immediately.

